\title{Linearly dependent vectors}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-08}
\taxon{definition}

\p{Let #{V} be a real vector space, let #{v_{1},\dots,v_{n}\in V}. We say these vectors are \define{Linearly dependent} if there are coefficients #{c_{1},\dots,c_{n}\in\RR} such that:}

##{c_{1}v_{1}+\dots+c_{n}v_{n}=\vec{0}}

\p{If there are no such coefficients, then we say #{v_{1}}, \dots, #{v_{n}} are \define{Linearly Independent}.}
